    <div class="container container--tool">
      <p>
        <strong>Reviewed by DoItSwift Editorial.</strong> The classic Latin word list is sourced from Cicero's <em>De finibus bonorum et malorum</em> (sections 1.10.32-33), the original passage that became the standard "Lorem Ipsum" placeholder text and is in the public domain. The English real-feel word list is curated from common English vocabulary. Non-Latin word lists for Hindi, Arabic, Chinese Simplified, Bengali, Spanish, and Russian use everyday-vocabulary words from the respective languages — they produce text with realistic character density and line-break behavior for layout testing, which is the purpose of placeholder text. Generation runs entirely in your browser using native JavaScript and the browser's Fetch API to load word lists from this same site — no text or input is sent to any server. Read our <a href="/about/editorial-policy/">editorial policy</a>, <a href="/about/how-we-research/">research methodology</a>, and <a href="/about/fact-checking/">fact-checking standards</a>.
